FT  14 NOV 94 / Business Travel: Flight of peace
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A new Irish air route opens on December 2 in the first big cross-border push
for travel business since the IRA ceasefire. Flights between Belfast and
Kerry will be a 'concrete example of the peace initiative at work', says Go
Ireland, the company promoting the service. It said: 'We would hope this is
the first of many such flights, opening new markets north and south of the
border.'
