FT  14 NOV 94 / Costs row halts Midlands project
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A dispute about future costs has stopped building work at the site of the
new headquarters of the Birmingham Midshires Building Society near
Wolverhampton, west Midlands, and led to the withdrawal of the contractor,
John Mowlem, from the project.
Mowlem has apologised to its sub-contractors and professional consultants,
all of whom had expected to see the project to completion.
But Midshires said a natural break had been reached in the project with the
completion of the shell-and-core work - the basic construction of the
building. 'We always had it mind to retain flexibility to bring the
fitting-out phase in-house,' it said.
