<HEADLINE>
FT  14 NOV 94 / Sane to build Pounds 6m research centre
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sane, the mental health charity, is to build a Pounds 6m centre in Oxford
for research into psychiatric illness.
The Prince of Wales International Centre for Research into Schizophrenia and
Depression will be funded mainly by overseas donors, including King Fahd of
Saudi Arabia and Mrs Stamatia Xylas, the Greek shipowner, who have each
given Pounds 1.75m.
Its planned research programme includes the genetics of schizophrenia, signs
in childhood of future psychotic illness and the relationship between mental
illness and asymmetry in the brain.
'We've learned more about the working of the brain in the last 10 years than
in the entire history of science,' said Prof Colin Blakemore, a scientific
adviser at the centre. 'Now we are on the brink of extending our knowledge
towards the conquest of brain disease.'
