<HEADLINE>
FT  14 NOV 94 / Iran takes Azeri oil stake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRYSTIA FREELAND
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Azeri and Iranian officials said over the weekend that Azerbaijan had agreed
to give Iran a 5 per cent stake in an international consortium for
developing Azeri oilfields in the Caspian Sea. The agreement, reached in
Baku, the Azeri capital will give Iran a quarter of Azerbaijan's 20 per cent
stake in the Dollars 7bn deal in exchange for financial and technical
assistance. Speaking on Radio Tehran, monitored by the BBC, Mr Gholamreza
Aghazadeh, Iran's oil minister, said he expected Iran to invest between
Dollars 300m and Dollars 350m in the project. Azeri officials told the
Russian news agency Interfax that Iran had been brought into the deal
because of Azerbaijan's inability to contribute its share of the financing.
