FT  12 NOV 94 / Reprieve for herbal remedies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Selling herbal remedies will continue to be legal, the government announced
yesterday.
The Medicines Control Agency - an executive agency of the health department
 -had said herbal medicines were covered by EU directives requiring their
licensing.
However, Mr Tom Sackville, junior health minister, said that because herbal
medicines were made by traditional processes, and not 'industrially
produced' as required by the directives, they could be exempted.
