<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 94 / Weekend Money (Financial Planning): Companies must tell -
Briefcase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
How can I find out if a public company is involved in litigation and, if so,
when and where the court proceedings will be held?
Ring it. Public companies are obliged to reveal details of any litigation
which has been initiated, whether court action is to be taken in this
country or abroad, and its estimated timetable. (Murray Johnstone Personal
Asset Management).
