<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 94 / Weekend Money (Companies): Directors' dealings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VIVIEN MACDONALD, Inside Track
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Buying at Everest Foods, noted last week, has continued.
The most recent transactions, by Christopher and John Fox Davies, came at
56p, the same as they paid previously. There has been no movement in the
share price.
The three directors buying at Country Casuals, the women's clothing
retailer, were taking the chance afforded them by the fall in the share
price after the announcement of interim results which reflected a fall from
pre-tax profit to loss.
The directors paid 84p; since then, the shares have rallied to over 90p.
Back in the spring, Richard Johnston, chief executive of Wyko Group, bought
120,000 shares at 45p.
Since then, the company has done well, outperforming the market by 26 per
cent over the past three months.
Now, chairman Philip White and Roger Edwards, a non-executive director, have
sold 400,000 shares each at 61.5p. Even so, their holdings still account for
almost 16 per cent of the group.
