<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
White pepper prices have tended firmer in recent weeks, reports Man
Producten, the main reason being the growing uncertainty about the size next
year's crops. The long drought in Indonesia will no doubt affect 1995
production, and supplies from China and Sarawak are gradually drying up.
Muntok white spot was priced at at USDollars 3,700 a tonne and for
November/December shipment at Dollars 3,650, cif. Black pepper prices tended
somewhat easier, mainly due to slow demand in recent weeks. Prices seem to
have stabilised at about Dollars 2,650 a tonne for spot black pepper faq and
at Dollars 2,575, cif, for November/December shipment. While supplies from
India and Indonesia were very limited there were more offers from Brazil.
</TEXT>
