FT  12 NOV 94 / Gambian rebellion put down
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BANJUL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Gambia's young military rulers yesterday foiled a coup attempt by junior
army officers in the west African tourist haven in which three plotters were
killed in a shootout. Lieutenant Yahya Jammeh, the 29-year-old military
strongman who toppled veteran president Sir Dawda Jawara in a bloodless coup
