<TEXT>
Ireland's coalition appeared on the point of breaking up last night after a
row over the appointment of a new president to the country's high court.
Labour walked out of a cabinet meeting called to discuss the appointment of
the attorney general, Mr Harry Whelehan, to the country's highest legal
